    "summary": "Bringing the passion for good (financial) reporting and supporting clients and our auditors in making the right choices. This is what I do since 2002, when I joined PwC\u2019s technical department (National Office) in Amsterdam, the Netherlands, after 13 years in the audit practice. I am a member/consultant at PwC\u2019s international network of IFRS specialists (Global Accounting Consulting Services).\nI use my expertise and joy in financial reporting, both IFRS and Dutch GAAP, in advising and supporting PwC clients and auditors: consulting on complex reporting topics, reviewing of financial statements, writing and publishing articles and contributing to manuals and study books. And finally, developing and providing trainings and educational sessions, internally and externally. \nAs of 2019 I am a member of the Dutch Accounting Standard Board (Raad voor de Jaarverslaggeving), the Dutch executive body responsible for improving of the quality of Dutch reporting, through the issuance of the Dutch Accounting Standards (Richtlijnen). \n",
